section.section:
"Exposure" means, as between a correctional employee and an inmate:
Percutaneous contact with blood, semen, or blood contaminated fluids;
Mucocutaneous contact with blood, semen, or blood contaminated fluids;
Open wound, including dermatitis, exudative lesions, or chapped skin, contact with blood, semen, or blood contaminated fluids; and
Intact skin contact with large amounts of blood, semen, or blood contaminated fluids for a prolonged period.

text.section:
An inmate shall furnish to the correctional institution a blood sample or buccal (cheek) swab to be tested for the presence of human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) when:
There has been an exposure involving the inmate;
The exposure occurred in connection with the inmate's violation of institutional regulations;
The inmate has been found guilty of the violation of institutional regulations described in paragraph (2) of this subsection;
The correctional employee involved in the exposure has given written notice of the exposure to the managing official of the correctional institution, or the official's designee; and
The exposure is confirmed by a health care provider.
